				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">/Melody (Uladaine's Official Guide!)<a name="75189"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 7 05 3:03 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>In case some of you bards don't know, there is a command that I find very, very wonderful for twisting sakes. /melody. Let me explain how this all works. as you all may know, spell songs are listed as numbers 1-9 *(if you have AA for 9)*, 1 being at top, going to 9 at the bottom spell on the bar. 
<br />

<br />
60 Bard (Virtuoso) Song lineup *(Normal Grouping)* 
<br />

<br />
------------------------------------------------ 
<br />
1) Katta's song of Sword Dancing (KSoSD) - Dex +Proc 
<br />
2) Composition of Ervaj (CoE) - Haste 
<br />
3) Warsong of the Vah Shir (WoVS) - Haste v3 
<br />
4) McVaxius` Rounding Rondo (MRR) - Haste v2 
<br />
5) Largos` Absonant Binding (LAB) - Snare / Slow 
<br />
6) Dreams of Ayonae (DoA) - Mezz 
<br />
7) Cassindra`s Chorus of Clarity (CCC) - Mana Regen 
<br />
8) Chorus of Replenishment (CoR) - HP+MP Regen 
<br />

<br />
This is one of my main basic song lineups. 
<br />

<br />
In my hotbutton bar, I have a hotkey that I made to twist 4 songs at one time without clicking my mouse a single time. Its simple, here is the layout of the hotbutton. 
<br />

<br />
Line 1 of my hotbutton is all you need, and simply place.... 
<br />

<br />
/melody x x x x 
<br />

<br />
where the X's are , you place the number slot of what song you are wanting to twist.... sooo... 
<br />

<br />
If i have.. 
<br />

<br />
/melody 1 2 3 4 
<br />

<br />
which is what i use. When i hit &quot;1&quot; to hit my 1st hotbutton i have it will cast song 1, then once it is on you as an effect, automatically it will stop singing, and move to the next number you have, slot 2 for me, then 3, then 4. and then it repeats. 
<br />

<br />
Melody works, and will keep twisting until you miss a note, and then you will have to start your chain of melody over. 
<br />

<br />
I hope this can be very useful to any of you who do not know about it, someone told me around level 46, and boy... did i so wish i knew it before &gt;&lt; hehe. Would save me ALOT of clicking on my mouse. Any questions just let me know =). 
<br />

<br />
Weird how Sony doesnt really put that info out there for you, like /melody, and the /autofire for rangers... when you first start your class... or maybe they do, its just been to long for me &gt;&lt; hehe
<br />

<br />
P.S. - Yes , this is usable starting level 1!!!</span></td>
